names.fullName: A protein-protein interaction network for human inherited ataxias and disorders of Purkinje cell degeneration.

confidence.value: Y2H interactions were divided into two classes based on the number of clones identified for each interacting protein. Core-1 interacting proteins were those for which more than three independent clones were found, whereas Core-2 had less than three clones.

attributeList.attribute: Lim J., Hao T., Shaw C., Patel AJ., Szabo G., Rual JF., Fisk CJ., Li N., Smolyar A., Hill DE., Barabasi AL., Vidal M., Zoghbi HY.

A total of 98 full-length or partial open reading frames (ORFs) were cloned into Gateway-compatible yeast two-hybrid Y2H destination vectors to generate GAL4 DNA binding domain(DB). Using these clones adult human brain cDNA libraries cloned into AD vectors were screened. The authors have reported a total of 674 interactions.

The gene symbols of the interacting proteins were used to parse the UniProtKB records and accession numbers for the UniProt records were obtained. The remaining records were checked for their symbol and gene ID in HGNC records, the UniProtKB accessions cross-referenced by Entrez gene or HGNC were used for these records.
